---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy - Sing for Hope"
  description="Learn about Sing for Hope's privacy practices and how we protect your personal information."
>
  <div class="bg-white">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="relative bg-gray-900">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-symphony to-symphonydark"></div>
      <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto py-24 px-4 sm:py-32 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Learn about our commitment to protecting your privacy and personal information.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Section -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Sing for Hope is committed to protecting your privacy and providing transparency about how we collect and use your information. We have created this Privacy Policy to explain our practices, policies, and procedures regarding the information we collect when you make a donation to us. This Privacy Policy applies to all information collected in regards to donations that occur both online and offline. We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time, so please check back periodically for changes. The date this Privacy Policy was last updated is stated at the end of this document.
          </p>
        </div>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-harmony mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
            Information Collection and Usage
          </h2>
          
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Anonymous Information</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              You can browse our site without logging on, and no personal information about you or your visit will be collected. Some anonymous, statistical information is automatically logged when you access our site. These "access logs" allow us to make our sites more useful to you and others who use them by, for example, tracking which features of the site are most used by visitors. None of this information, which is listed below, is associated with any personal information or contains anything identifying you personally:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
              <li>The date of the visit</li>
              <li>The time of arrival and length of visit</li>
              <li>The browser used (e.g., Chrome, AOL, Netscape, Safari, etc.)</li>
              <li>A list of files downloaded or pages viewed and/or errors encountered</li>
              <li>The Internet Protocol (IP) address of the machine through which the site was accessed</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Use of Cookies</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              A cookie is an alphanumeric identifier that is automatically stored on the hard drive of a computer that accesses a website. It allows our system to recognize your browser's access privileges and to personalize your session with us. We use cookies to improve your experience on our site and to understand how you and others interact with our site. We do not share information from cookies with any third parties. You may adjust the settings on your browser to decline cookies, but doing so may limit the features that are available to you on our site.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Online and Offline Donations</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Sing for Hope collects the following personal information through our secure online financial-transaction pages as well as offline when appropriate: name, address, e-mail address, phone number, and credit card information. This personal information is used to process your donation, communicate with you about your donation, and acknowledge receipt of your donation for tax purposes. In addition, we may use such information to improve our marketing efforts or to contact you and send you information regarding Sing for Hope through email updates and mailings.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-harmony/10 border border-harmony/20 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-gray-800 font-medium">
                We will not sell, share or trade our donors' names or personal information with any other entity nor send mailings to our donors on behalf of other organizations. This policy applies to all information received by Sing for Hope, both online and offline, on any Platform ("Platform" includes the Sing for Hope website and mobile applications), as well as any electronic, written, or oral communications.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Personal Information</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              When you make a donation or volunteer in one of our programs, we collect the information necessary to process the transaction: name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, and, when applicable, credit card number. For security reasons, we do not share credit card information with any third parties or store it permanently on our web server. If you register on our site but do not make a donation or volunteer commitment, we collect the same information except for credit card information.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Your name and contact information will be added to our database, and we may perform statistical analyses of user behavior to measure interest in the various areas of our site. You may receive direct mail or emails from Sing for Hope.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-melody mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 7.89a1 1 0 001.42 0L21 7M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z" />
            </svg>
            Contact Us
          </h2>
          <div class="bg-melody/5 border border-melody/20 rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              If you have specific questions or concerns about Sing for Hope's Privacy Policy, to review your personal information, or to opt out of future mailings, please contact us at:
            </p>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-melody/20">
              <p class="text-gray-800 font-medium">
                <strong>Sing for Hope</strong><br>
                99 Wall Street #1812<br>
                New York, New York 10005<br>
                Email: <a href="mailto:hello@singforhope.org" class="text-melody hover:text-melodydark">hello@singforhope.org</a><br>
                Phone: <a href="tel:212-966-5955" class="text-melody hover:text-melodydark">212-966-5955</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-rhythm mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15" />
            </svg>
            Changes to Our Privacy Policy
          </h2>
          <div class="bg-rhythm/5 border border-rhythm/20 rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              We reserve the right to revise this Privacy Policy at any time by updating this posting. Please check back regularly to see if there have been any changes to our Privacy Policy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="mt-16 text-center text-sm text-gray-500 border-t pt-8">
          <p>Last updated: January 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>